s, OAuth2WebClient might become necessary. I need to check class references to see if it can compile without the optional dependency. If tests attempt to call OAuth2WebClient.create, the optional dependency could be crucial. I'll also look into the runtime arguments to understand the issues with the current versions and stacktrace details.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking build settings for coverage**\\n\\nThe existing build only sets arguments if the library version is 5.0.0. Since I'm testing with version 5.0.1, the condition is false, and no arguments are set. Vert.x 5.0.1 still uses Netty 4.2.x, so the generated test needs to set system properties in the native test runtime arguments for 5.0.1. This raises the question: is this necessary before achieving meaningful test coverage? The tests can run on the JVM, but they fail natively without the proper setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying documentation for tests**\\n\\nI realize I need to ensure that the generated tests set the correct properties in agent_guidance, which makes me think about the action around advisory_preparation. So, I should probably verify the documentation for Netty’s Java 24/25 regarding sun.misc.unsafe.memory.access. It sounds like it's best to search through my local repository or its documentation to double-check the details. This way, I could ensure everything aligns!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3wp2krNdo5oS0Za3d0vVGnS0|fc_0cb5150abef47f2a016a3eff4cf7888194a4539835bac1ad74", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"sun\\.misc\\.unsafe\\.memory\\.access|tryReflectionSetAccessible|Vert.x 5.0.0 pulls\" -n .", "timeout": 10}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4kGKDiz88bXgAdsvUdhkFjEI|fc_0cb5150abef47f2a016a3eff4cf7a081949ee93bcbe21982c9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport subprocess, re\njars=list(Path.home().glob('.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.netty/netty-common/4.2.2.Final/*/netty-common-4.2.2.Final.jar'))\nprint(jars)\nif jars:\n out=subprocess.check_output(['jar','tf',str(jars[0])], text=True)\n for name in out.splitlines():\n  if 'PlatformDependent' in name or 'Cleaner' in name or 'Unsafe' in name:\n   print(name)\nPY", "timeout": 10}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nAmdvh9JHP0RdngYELqHWxQx|fc_0cb5150abef47f2a016a3eff4cf7a88194a480bcb5198322c6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re,html\nreq=urllib.request.Request('https://vertx.io/docs/vertx-web-client/java/', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','ignore')\n# extract text snippets containing key phrases\ntext=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',data)\ntext=html.unescape(re.sub('\\s+',' ',text))\nfor phrase in ['Web Client', 'Create a web client', 'Sending requests', 'WebClient.create', 'The web client']:\n idx=text.find(phrase)\n print('\\nPHRASE', phrase, 'IDX', idx)\n print(text[idx:idx+1000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4142, "output": 970, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26616, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782513472755, "responseId": "resp_0cb5150abef47f2a016a3eff4134188194a5ccaa767a54ff1a"}}
